I did some further investigations. In order to establish connection between provider and consumer, we have to do several things:

* On the provider side: declare `CpuUsageService` on provider side, which expose the service to consumers.

```xml
    <dubbo:service interface="org.apache.dubbo.rpc.cluster.loadbalance.statistics.CpuUsageService" ref="cpuUsageService" connections="1" callbacks="1000">
        <dubbo:method name="addListener">
            <dubbo:argument index="1" callback="true" />
        </dubbo:method>
    </dubbo:service>
```

* On the consumer side, we have to programmably get the reference to `CpuUsageService`. Because in the dubbo-cluster module we cannot depend on a high level `ReferenceConfig` API in dubbo-config, so we have to use some low level APIs, which can be found at `org.apache.dubbo.monitor.dubbo.DubboMonitorFactory#createMonitor`.

The idea is that first randomly pick an invoker, and generate a proxy of `CpuUsageService` on that provider, then add the listener to that provider. Once we got enough stats, we can implement the load balance based on the stats.

```java

    @Override
    protected <T> Invoker<T> doSelect(List<Invoker<T>> invokers, URL url, Invocation invocation) {

        int index = (int)(invokers.size() * Math.random());
        Invoker<T> invoker = invokers.get(index);
        cpuUsage.computeIfAbsent(invoker.getUrl().getAddress(), value -> {
            URLBuilder urlBuilder = URLBuilder.from(invoker.getUrl());
            urlBuilder.setPath(CpuUsageService.class.getName());
            urlBuilder.addParameter(INTERFACE_KEY, CpuUsageService.class.getName());
            urlBuilder.addParameter("bean.name", CpuUsageService.class.getName());
            urlBuilder.addParameter(METHODS_KEY, "addListener,removeListener");
            urlBuilder.addParameters(CHECK_KEY, String.valueOf(false), REFERENCE_FILTER_KEY, "");
            urlBuilder.addParameter("addListener.1.callback", true);
            Invoker<CpuUsageService> cpuUsageInvoker = protocol.refer(CpuUsageService.class, urlBuilder.build());
            CpuUsageService cpuUsageService = proxyFactory.getProxy(cpuUsageInvoker);
            cpuUsageService.addListener("statisticsloadbalance", new CpuUsageListenerImpl());
            return 0.0f;
        });

        // TODO implement the load balance with statistics provided by the service provider.
        return invoker;
    }

    public void setProtocol(Protocol protocol) {
        this.protocol = protocol;
    }

    public void setProxyFactory(ProxyFactory proxyFactory) {
        this.proxyFactory = proxyFactory;
    }
```

Note that:

1. `protocol` and `proxyFactory` can be auto-wired, if you provider setters.
2. Not every parameters in URL matters, please explore it, however `addListener.1.callback` is important for the provider and consumer communication, it let them know that the second parameter of addListener method is a callback.
3. It is just a demo code, it is not mature, please improve it.
4. It better to use a dedicated class to implement `CpuUsageListener`, or there will be some issue during the serialization of provider-consumer communication.

